Care -- tComment On The Paper of Mckeown -- tConclusion0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWhat moral and legal issues are involved in the physician-patient relationship? What is bioethics? What social and environmental factors are involved in health and disease? An interdisciplinary workshop of the Calgary Institute for the Humanities in May 1980 considered these issues, as well as health care delivery, the history of public health in Canada, conflicting "health cultures," and responsibilities of professionals on the health care team. Participating in the conference were prominent scholars and professionals in social edicine, community health, nursing, law, medical research, medical education, and various academic disciplines. They included Dr. Thomas McKeown, Dr. David Roy, Professor Hazel Weidman, Professor Benjamin Freedman, Dr. Anthony Lam, and Dr. Robert Hatfield.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMedical carevCongresses. 0aMedical carezCanadavCongresses. 0aPhysician and patientvCongresses. 0aPhysician and patientzCanadavCongresses. 4aMedical. 4aPolitical Science: Social Policy. 4aSocial Science. 7aMEDICAL / Physician & Patient.2bisacsh1 aBrown, Malcolm C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharles, Cathy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrichton, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlaherty, M. Josephine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFpeedman, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGelfand, Toby, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHatfield, Robert E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/re